@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{keredomo}}}} is a disjunctive subordinate conjunction that joins two sentences.
the basic meaning is "although."

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{bamboo^inside}}san'ni@KJ{{electricity^tale}}wokaketa@EM{{keredo}}
      @KJ{{detain^guard}}deshita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I phoned Takeuchi but she was out.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{book}}ha@KJ{{tall}}i@EM{{keredomo}}ii@KJ{{book}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Although this book is expensive, it's a good book.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
At the end of a sentence @HI{{@EM{{keredomo}}}} implies something exists that qualifies what is actually said.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{tamaniha@KJ{{trip^going}}nimo@KJ{{going}}kitaito@KJ{{think}}tteirundesu@EM{{kedo}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'd really like to go on a trip once in a while (but I don't have the time).
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{keredomo}}}} can be used to delimit a preliminary remark.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{mada@KJ{{discharge^car}}made1@KJ{{time^interval}}mouarimasu@EM{{kedo}},
